  "prompt": "Does Fab currently offer new employees stock options or RSUs?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, Fab (a design-focused e-commerce platform) does not publicly disclose specific details about its compensation packages, including whether it offers new employees stock options or Restricted Stock Units (RSUs). Compensation policies can vary depending on the company's stage, funding, and strategic priorities.\n\nTo get accurate and up-to-date information, I recommend:\n\n1. **Reviewing job postings**: Sometimes, companies include details about equity compensation in job descriptions.  \n2. **Asking during the interview process**: You can inquire directly about stock options, RSUs, or other equity incentives.  \n3. **Checking resources like Glassdoor or LinkedIn**: Current or former employees may share insights about compensation practices.  \n\nFor the most accurate answer, contacting Fab directly or consulting a recruiter familiar with the company would be ideal.",
